Sql identifiers
—————

Sql identifiers are names used to identify database object such as 
Database names, table names,column names,view names, index names, constraints,triggers,stored
Procedures..etc…

While we are declaring identifiers we have to fallow some rules and regulations.

1.⁠ ⁠the only allowed characters to define identifiers 1-z,A-Z,0-9,_,$.
2.⁠ ⁠must be begin with letter or underscore(_)
3.⁠ ⁠we cant declare identifiers with reversed words.
4.⁠ ⁠spaces are not considered to declare identifiers.
5.⁠ ⁠identifiers are case sensitive.
6.⁠ ⁠max length to declare identifiers are 15 characters.

SQL
====
Sql is a( structured query language ) is standardised programming language specifically designed 
For managing and manipulating relational databases.it provides a declarative syntax that allows 
User to define what data they want retrieve, insert, update ,or delete without specifying exactly 
How databases should execute these operations,


Sql commands
————
Types of sql commands

1.DDL(data definition language)
==========
DDL commands are used to define, create, modify and delete the structure of a database objects
Such as databases,tabales,views,and constraints./

->create:-by using these command to create a new databases, tables, views, indexes..etc.
Alter--> by using alter command we can modifies the structure of an existing table. like(add ,drop,rename coloumns, modify datatype, add constraints)
drop--> deletes an entire database object perminently like (databases, tables, view, indexes ..ect)
truncate--> by using truncatecommand delete all records from a table without deleting the table.
rename--> it is used to rename the database object names.

2.DML(data manipulation language)
=============
manages data stores within database objects.

insert--> by using insert command we can insert some records into a tavble.
update--> by using the update command we can update some records based on some conditions.
delete--> by using the delete command we can delete some records based on some conditions.
lock--> controls concurrency by locking a table restrict accesses from other transactions while it
        is being modified

3.DCL(data control language)
=======
manages permissions and access control on database objects.

grant--> gives specific proviledges or permissions(such select,update,insert,delete,all privilagoues) to a database user or role.
revoke--> removes previously granted permission from database user or role, restricting their access to database objects.

4.TCL
==========
manages transactions to maintain data integrity.

commit--> perminently saves all changes made during the current transactions to the database. making them visible to other users.
rollback--> undoes/revert changes made during the current transaction back to the last committed state or a savepoint in case of an error.

Savepoint
_______
set a temporary market within a transaction to you which you can later rollback ,without undoing the entire transaction.

5.DQL
=======
used to fetch or retrieve data from the databases.

select--> retrieves data from 1 or more tables or views based on specified coloumns and conditons. it is the most frequently used in SQL.
